title: Najibullah Zadran and Mohammad Nabi boost Afghanistan to victory
text:
Najibullah Zadran and Mohammad Nabi boost Afghanistan to victory 26 Oct 2015 14:31:52 
comments 
An unbeaten half-century stand between Najibullah Zadran and Mohammad Nabi steered Afghanistan to a six-wicket win over Zimbabwe in the opening T20 International in Bulawayo. 
Zadran (37) and Nabi (33) put on an unbroken 69 for the fifth wicket to steer Afghanistan from 85 for four to 154 without further loss, Zadran claiming the winning runs with a six off the first ball of the final over. 
Sikandar Raza (59) and Chamu Chibhabha (54) had put on a century for the first wicket before the hosts subsided to 153 for five, Dawlat Zadran finishing with three for 29. Related Sport News
